The new president of Ikeja Club, Chief Ayodeji Randle, has called on the federal and state governments to support efforts at ameliorating the plight of Nigerians, especially during this COVID-19 pandemic.
 
He also stated the need for private enterprises and social organisations to undertake projects that would transform lives of citizens through provision of infrastructure, especially those aimed at enhancing health and social well-being of citizens.
 
Randle made the calls shortly after he was inaugurated as the 21st president of Ikeja Club.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .